#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: head-field-shadow
---

# List.head must survive a case-class field named `head` in another module

Regression for the busi hub-boot blocker `Op("Nil.trim", (), <closure>)` on the
v2 VM: importing a module that defines `case class Ref(name: String, head: String)`
(field `head` at index 1) made `hits.head` on a LIST resolve through the field
accessor — by FIELD INDEX — so a one-element list yielded Nil (element #1 does
not exist) and the downstream `.trim` became an unhandled effect Op. With `head`
as the FIRST field the bug hides (index 0 = first element). v1 lanes are correct;
this pins the semantics. Found minimizing busi src/v2/http/context.ssc
(busiCfGet) × core/repo_commit.ssc (RepoRef).

[mkRef](./lib/head-field-box.ssc)

```scalascript
val lines = "dataDir=/tmp/x\nport=8394".split("\n").toList

def cfGet(key: String, dflt: String): String =
  val hits = lines.filter(l => l.startsWith(key + "="))
  if hits.isEmpty then dflt else hits.head.drop(key.length + 1).trim

println(cfGet("dataDir", "?"))
println(cfGet("port", "?"))
println(cfGet("missing", "dflt"))
val r = mkRef("main", "abc123")
println(r.head)
println(List("only").head)
```
